This paper is about machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a neural network model for this task, which involves multi-step reasoning and prediction. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
